{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2191f60a-9edc-40f8-93f0-407e6ca862be","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .NET crash dump! Unfortunately, I don't have a specialized skill for **analyzing** dumps (only for collecting them), but here's how you can do it:\n\n## Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, CLI)\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>\n   ```\n   Key commands inside the analyzer:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n   - `pe` — print the last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all managed threads\n   - `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows, most powerful)\n   - Load the dump, then `!analyze -v` for automated crash analysis\n   - `.loadby sos clr` (Framework) or `.loadby sos coreclr` (modern .NET)\n\n3. **Visual Studio** — Open the `.dmp` file directly for a GUI experience with \"Debug with Managed Only\"\n\n## Typical Investigation Flow\n\n1. **`pe`** — check if there's an unhandled exception (most common crash cause)\n2. **`clrstack`** — see what code was running when it crashed\n3. **`threads`** — look for deadlocks or thread pool exhaustion\n4. **`dumpheap -stat`** — check for memory issues (OOM crashes)\n\nWould you like me to try running `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file if you can tell me its path? Or do you need help with a specific step?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"baae338f-f2e2-4923-86ad-381b955b1ea6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file and wants to analyze it. Let me look at what tools and skills are available to help with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for *collecting* crash dumps, not analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\n\nNone of the available skills directly support dump analysis, so I'll need to guide the user toward the appropriate tools like dotnet-dump analyze, WinDbg, lldb, or Visual Studio depending on their platform and whether this is a .NET dump.\n\nSince the user mentioned they already have the file but didn't specify its location or format details, I should ask where it's stored and what type of dump it is so I can provide more targeted advice.","outputTokens":756,"requestId":"6080:C5472:2FDA53:3E8AB1:69FFE5B7"},"id":"bf031574-db7b-40dd-905e-6972f951ed46","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:56:25.871Z","parentId":"b83aae05-9886-4874-b2cb-550514dba379"}
